  "original_title": "Casino Business \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Amendment to the Casino Business Act",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Gambling Industry (Regulation), Betting and Gambling Levy Act provides for the regulation of the gambling industry in Sri Lanka.",
        "Although licenses are required to carry on the card business in Sri Lanka, no card business has yet been granted licenses under the said Act as orders have not yet been issued to strengthen the provisions of the said Act.",
        "Under this situation, it is difficult to carry out tax deductions in a proper manner from the companies that are currently carrying out the business of card games.",
        "Therefore, the Cabinet has given approval to introduce appropriate amendments and take necessary steps under the Lottery Industry, Betting and Gambling Levy Act to regulate such businesses and levy the relevant tax to be levied by the Government.",
        "The idea submitted by Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe as Minister of Finance, Economic Stability and National Policies has been approved."
      ],
